Czech Minister May Use Subsidies for Housing Savings, HN Says

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-04-28T06:51:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/czech-minister-may-use-subsidies-for-housing-savings-hn-says.html
Czech Finance Minister Miroslav Kalousek may use flood subsidies or similar financial means to
reimburse construction savings subsidies previously reduced by
the government,  Hospodarske Noviny  reported, citing Kalousek.  The minister is also drafting a bill that would limit using
money from construction savings only for housing purposes, the
newspaper said.  The Constitutional Court ruled yesterday that the state
must reimburse the full construction savings subsidies for last
year, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net ; 